y, this book offers a methodology which leaps productively from causal hypotheses in plural travelling theories to explanations of locally observable events. It is exemplified in interrogating the poly-contextual formation of the artworld in Beijing as a conjunctive multiplicity.  afunded by Technische Universität Berlin  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aArt. 4aArtworld. 4aChina. 4aCritical Realism. 4aScience. 4aSociology of Art. 4aSociology of Knowledge. 4aSociology. 4aSpace. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aArt.  aArtworld.  aChina.  aCritical Realism.  aScience.  aSociology of Art.  aSociology of Knowledge.  aSociology.  aSpace.2 aTechnische Universität Berlinefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z978311076731540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839455876zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839455876zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839455876/original  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-